## Segment 3: 00:17.900 => 00:31.500
Gal Gadot talks about her apprehension towards the Miss Universe pageant.

Transcript
```
WEBVTT

00:10.400 --> 00:17.920
<Speaker 2 Speaker>I went for the experience, and then I won, and I was overwhelmed, and then I had to do the Miss Universe pageant.
00:17.960 --> 00:22.600
<Speaker 2 Speaker>And then I was freaking out that I'm gonna win this, that pageant as well, because I wasn't...
00:22.960 --> 00:23.640
<Speaker 2 Speaker>thinking about women.
00:23.640 --> 00:24.600
<Speaker 1 Speaker>Oh, you didn't want to win?
00:24.600 --> 00:28.880
<Speaker 2 Speaker>No, so I set myself a mission not to win the Miss Universe pageant.
00:28.880 --> 00:29.160
<Speaker 1 Speaker>Okay.
00:29.320 --> 00:30.600
<Speaker 2 Speaker>Which meant, so I just...
00:30.600 --> 00:32.520
<Speaker 1 Speaker>You threw the Miss Universe pageant.
```

description.valueString: The video begins with Jimmy Kimmel, the host, interviewing Gal Gadot, an actress. Jimmy Kimmel is seen asking Gal about her experience as Miss Israel when she was a teenager. Gal Gadot confirms that she was Miss Israel and begins to explain how she ended up in the beauty pageant. The conversation is light-hearted, with Jimmy Kimmel appearing engaged and curious about Gal's past experiences.

Gal Gadot continues to share her story about participating in the Miss Israel pageant. She explains that she was offered to participate and went for the experience, unexpectedly winning the title. She describes feeling overwhelmed and having to participate in the Miss Universe pageant, which she was apprehensive about winning.

Gal Gadot elaborates on her feelings about the Miss Universe pageant, expressing her fear of winning it. She humorously mentions that she set a mission not to win the Miss Universe pageant, indicating that she was not interested in pursuing a career in pageantry.

Jimmy Kimmel humorously questions Gal Gadot about her strategy to not win the Miss Universe pageant. Gal responds by saying she is not the type of girl who would want to win such a pageant, indicating her disinterest in the pageant world. The segment includes a light-hearted exchange between the two.

The video transitions to a scene showing a group of women in pageant dresses, including Gal Gadot, during the Miss Universe pageant. Jimmy Kimmel comments on the scene, noting that it doesn't look like Gal's heart was in it, suggesting her lack of enthusiasm for the pageant. The segment ends with a close-up of Gal Gadot in the pageant setting.
